e%20specialist%2C%20Teddy%20had%20a%2023-hour%20electroencephalogram%20(EEG)%2C%20a%20test%20that%20detects%20electrical%20activity%20in%20the%20brain%20and%20can%20help%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fwhat-causes-seizures%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ediagnose%20epilepsy%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20doctor%20saw%20the%20results%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BHis%20brain%20is%20really%20busy.%26quot%3B%20He%20didn't%20mean%20it%20in%20a%20good%20way.%20It%20was%20as%20if%20the%20doctor%20could%20see%20that%20his%20symptoms%20were%20about%20to%20really%20kick%20off.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Teddy%20sitting%20at%20the%20kitchen%20table%20and%20smiling.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663bcebb9686a6f37bfd60a6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221152%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETeddy%20has%20seen%20a%20reduction%20in%20his%20seizures%20since%20receiving%20the%20brain%20implant.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20Children's%20Nebraska%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221097ae87-b0c7-4478-bf50-2d42348a3799%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20tried%20to%20start%20medications%20early%2C%20but%20nothing%20worked%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETeddy%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20Lennox-Gastaut%20syndrome%2C%20a%20severe%20form%20of%20epilepsy.%20He%20was%20put%20on%20medication%2C%20but%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-to-do-someone-is-having-a-seizure-2018-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehis%20seizures%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20just%20became%20more%20intense%20and%20frequent.%20Medications%20did%20little%20to%20help.%20From%20the%20time%20he%20was%20about%20a%20year%20and%20a%20half%20until%20he%20was%203%2C%20he%20was%20having%20more%20seizures%20than%20we%20could%20count%20every%20day.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEvery%20time%20he%20fell%20asleep%20or%20woke%20up%2C%20he'd%20have%20a%20cluster%20of%20seizures.%20His%20head%20would%20droop%2C%20and%20his%20body%20would%20fall%20forward.%20In%20most%20cases%2C%20this%20would%20have%20been%20a%20reason%20for%20a%20trip%20to%20the%20ER%2C%20but%20if%20we%20went%20to%20the%20hospital%20every%20time%20Teddy%20had%20a%20seizure%2C%20we%20would%20have%20been%20living%20there.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInstead%2C%20we%20worked%20closely%20with%20our%20doctors%20at%20Children's%20Nebraska%2C%20which%20is%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.childrensnebraska.org%2Fdepartment%2Fepilepsy-center%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Elevel%204%20epilepsy%20center%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20highest%20designation%20available.%20We%20also%20consulted%20with%20epilepsy%20doctors%20around%20the%20country.%20We%20tried%20so%20many%20medications%2C%20but%20none%20worked.%20We%20were%20constantly%20weaning%20Teddy%20onto%20or%20off%20of%20new%20medicines.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELooking%20back%2C%20we%20were%20in%20a%20fight-or-flight%20response.%20But%20we%20were%20also%20learning%20to%20listen%20to%20our%20intuition%20as%20Teddy's%20parents.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b3b1a5fe-22cc-490e-a2c4-46bd2390f467%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EDoctors%20told%20us%20to%20act%20fast%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20Teddy%20was%20three%2C%20I%20listened%20to%20a%20podcast%20where%20a%20doctor%20talked%20about%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoctors-disconnect-half-6-year-old-girls-brain-stop-seizures-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esurgical%20management%20for%20epilepsy%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Despite%20the%20fact%20that%20Teddy%20didn't%20respond%20to%20medications%2C%20we%20had%20never%20been%20offered%20surgical%20options%2C%20which%20are%20seen%20as%20a%20last%20resort.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20reached%20out%20to%20the%20doctor%20I'd%20heard%20speak%20on%20the%20podcast%20and%20then%20to%20another%20specialist.%20Both%20agreed%20that%20a%20surgical%20implant%20might%20help.%20It%20wouldn't%20stop%20his%20seizures%20completely%2C%20but%20it%20could%20vastly%20reduce%20them.%20That%20meant%20his%20brain%20would%20have%20a%20chance%20to%20grow%20and%20develop%2C%20just%20like%20other%20preschoolers.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20of%20the%20doctors%20said%20something%20that%20really%20resonated%20with%20me%3A%20%26quot%3BYou%20have%20a%20kid%20whose%20brain%20is%20on%20fire.%20My%20recommendation%20is%20to%20act%20fast.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Teddy%20wearing%20a%20hat%20and%20looking%20at%20his%20father%20while%20smiling%20and%20standing%20outside.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663bcee79686a6f37bfd60cb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETeddy%2C%20now%206%2C%20has%20made%20a%20lot%20of%20progress%20since%20the%20surgery.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20Children's%20Nebraska%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b06d3a87-ba00-4d06-8d21-946c4910ab88%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20knew%20if%20we%20didn't%20do%20something%2C%20I%20worried%20Teddy%20would%20die%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20knew%20the%20doctor%20was%20right.%20Yet%20the%20treatment%20we%20were%20considering%2C%20a%20brain%20implant%20called%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epilepsy.com%2Ftreatment%2Fdevices%2Fresponsive-neurostimulation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eresponsive%20neurostimulation%20(RNS)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20was%20only%20approved%20for%20adults.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBecause%20I'm%20a%20nurse%20practitioner%2C%20I%20understand%20that%20medications%20are%20often%20used%20off-label%2C%20meaning%20not%20in%20the%20way%20that%20they're%20formally%20approved%20for.%20I%20use%20off-label%20medications%20in%20the%20NICU%20all%20the%20time%2C%20and%20they%20help%20my%20patients.%20So%2C%20I%20was%20somewhat%20comfortable%20using%20the%20RNS%20treatment%20off-label%2C%20with%20the%20doctors'%20recommendation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20more%20important%20was%20my%20mother's%20intuition.%20I%20just%20knew%20that%20if%20we%20didn't%20do%20something%20drastic%20to%20help%20Teddy%2C%20he%20would%20die.%20I%20had%20seen%20other%20families%20whose%20children%20had%20died%2C%20and%20I%20worried%20that%20was%20the%20road%20we%20were%20on%2C%20even%20if%20doctors%20weren't%20explicitly%20saying%20that.%20My%20husband%20and%20I%20decided%20to%20try%20the%20surgery.%20Years%20later%2C%20people%20still%20can't%20believe%20we%20took%20that%20risk%2C%20but%20we%20felt%20that%20not%20taking%20it%20would%20have%20meant%20giving%20up%20on%20Teddy%2C%20and%20there%20was%20no%20way%20I%20could%20give%20up%20on%20my%20son.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bc789f9e-addd-42e2-b17b-76792ef86b0a%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ETeddy%20is%20thriving%2C%20and%20he's%20changed%20how%20I%20approach%20my%20work%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20process%20wasn't%20smooth.%20Teddy's%20initial%20surgery%20was%20in%20Los%20Angeles.%20When%20his%20incision%20became%20infected%2C%20doctors%20needed%20to%20remove%20a%20large%20part%20of%20the%20implant.%20Later%2C%20he%20was%20reimplanted%20at%20Children's%20Nebraska.%20At%20only%203%20years%20old%2C%20he%20was%20the%20youngest%20child%20in%20the%20country%20to%20have%20an%20RNS%20implant.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt's%20been%20two%20years%20since%20Teddy%20had%20his%20second%20implantation%20surgery%2C%20and%20the%20results%20have%20been%20amazing.%20Before%20surgery%2C%20his%20preschool%20teacher%20needed%20to%20give%20him%20rescue%20medication%20to%20stop%20seizures%20three%20times%20a%20week.%20This%20year%2C%20he's%20only%20had%20one%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdiagnosed-epilepsy-seizures-studying-abroad-paris-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eseizure%20at%20school%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETeddy%20is%20in%20kindergarten%2C%20and%20he%20is%20thriving.%20He%20uses%20a%20walker%20to%20get%20around%20school%20and%20recently%20said%20%26quot%3BHello%26quot%3B%20to%20his%20teacher%2C%20who%20just%20about%20fell%20out%20of%20his%20chair%20with%20surprise.%20Most%20importantly%2C%20he's%20bonding%20with%20his%20fellow%20students.%20Just%20this%20week%2C%20a%20neighbor%20in%20his%20grade%20brought%20over%20birthday%20cupcakes%20to%20share%20with%20him.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERaising%20Teddy%20has%20changed%20how%20I%20talk%20with%20NICU%20families%20facing%20serious%20medical%20diagnoses.%20Before%2C%20I%20was%20focused%20on%20whether%20kids%20could%20achieve%20certain%20activities%20of%20daily%20life.%20Now%2C%20I%20understand%20that%20families%20just%20love%20their%20children.%20Disability%20isn't%20a%20negative%20word.%20These%20kids%20are%20amazing%2C%20vibrant%20members%20of%20our%20families%20and%20society%2C%20and%20we're%20so%20lucky%20to%20have%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fson-seizures-brain-implant-success-story-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715515562000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663bcfbef27898f532d5305f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fson-seizures-brain-implant-success-story-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Liz%20Bronson's%20son%20had%20seizures%20multiple%20times%20a%20day%20and%20medication%20didn't%20help.%20A%20brain%20implant%20helped%20and%20he's%20now%20walking%20and%20tal