o%20pin%20all%20the%20blame%20on%20Michael%20Cohen.%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-hush-money-trial-hope-hicks-witness-stand-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etestimony%20from%20Trump's%20former%20press%20secretary%20and%20aide%20Hope%20Hicks%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20after%20the%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20first%20published%20articles%20about%20the%20hush-money%20arrangement%20in%202018%2C%20Trump%20said%20Cohen%20%26quot%3Bdid%20it%20out%20of%20the%20kindness%20of%20his%20own%20heart%26quot%3B%20to%20%26quot%3Bprotect%20him%26quot%3B%20but%20%26quot%3Bnever%20told%20anybody%20about%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20questioning%20his%20former%20employees%2C%20Trump's%20lawyers%20consistently%20ask%20whether%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Bmultitasking%26quot%3B%20while%20signing%20checks.%20And%20under%20questioning%20from%20a%20prosecutor%2C%20Hicks%20offered%20that%20Trump%20would%20have%20a%20constant%20flow%20of%20people%20coming%20in%20and%20out%20of%20his%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20is%20a%20very%20good%20multitasker%20and%20a%20very%20hard%20worker%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BHe%20is%20always%20doing%20many%20things%20at%20once.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20attorney%20Susan%20Necheles%20drilled%20into%20the%20question%20Friday%20while%20Madeleine%20Westerhout%2C%20Trump's%20White%20House%20executive%20assistant%20who%20kept%20a%20desk%20right%20outside%20the%20Oval%20Office%2C%20was%20on%20the%20witness%20stand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20didn't%20use%20a%20computer%20and%20requested%20hard%20copies%20of%20everything.%20He%20%26quot%3Bfelt%20that%20if%20someone%20was%20getting%20his%20signature%2C%20they%20deserved%20his%20real%20signature%2C%26quot%3B%20Necheles%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWesterhout%20agreed%20Trump%20was%20%26quot%3Ba%20person%20who%20multitasked%26quot%3B%20and%20signed%20%26quot%3Bcommissions%2C%20proclamations%2C%20executive%20orders%2C%20memos%2C%20and%20other%20documents%26quot%3B%20throughout%20the%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wouldn't%20be%20unusual%2C%20she%20said%2C%20if%20Trump%20signed%20a%20stack%20of%20documents%20while%20meeting%20with%20members%20of%20his%20administration%20or%20even%20foreign%20leaders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20secure%20a%20felony%20conviction%2C%20prosecutors%20need%20to%20convince%20jurors%20that%20Trump%20knew%20what%20the%20money%20was%20for%3A%20That%20whenever%20he%20signed%20a%20check%20to%20Cohen%2C%20it%20was%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20reimbursing%20him%20for%20the%20Stormy%20Daniels%20hush%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20Trump%20may%20not%20seem%20like%20the%20most%20detail-oriented%20person%2C%20prosecutors%20say%20there's%20something%20he's%20always%20watching%3A%20the%20bottom%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221b635192-54d8-4265-9195-c9b8811fcee0%5C%22%3ETrump%20was%20discerning%20about%20which%20checks%20he%20signed%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20made%20no%20secret%20of%20his%20parsimoniousness.%20He%20has%20bragged%20about%20not%20paying%20vendors%20for%20his%20buildings.%20And%20he%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-legal-fees-pac-donor-money-personal-cases-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eusing%20political%20donor%20money%20to%20pay%20his%20lawyers%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProsecutors%20presented%20excerpts%20from%20Trump's%20book%20%26quot%3BThink%20Like%20a%20Billionaire%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20includes%20a%20chapter%20titled%20%26quot%3BHow%20to%20Pinch%20Pennies.%26quot%3B%20In%20it%2C%20Trump%20relayed%20a%20famous%20story%20where%20he%20cashed%20a%2050-cent%20check%20from%20Spy%20magazine%2C%20winning%20its%20%26quot%3Bcheapest%20millionaire%26quot%3B%20contest.%20Every%20check%20counts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20always%20sign%20my%20checks%2C%20so%20I%20know%20where%20my%20money's%20going%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20the%20same%20spirit%2C%20I%20also%20always%20try%20to%20read%20my%20bills%20to%20make%20sure%20I'm%20not%20being%20overcharged.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20book%20%E2%80%94%20which%20defense%20attorneys%20were%20sure%20to%20point%20out%20was%20written%20with%20the%20help%20of%20a%20ghostwriter%20%E2%80%94%20Trump%20reflected%20deeply%20on%20budgeting%2C%20even%20musing%20about%20the%20innate%20ethics%20of%20room%20decorators.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20are%20working%20with%20a%20decorator%2C%20make%20sure%20you%20ask%20to%20see%20all%20of%20the%20invoices%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BDecorators%20are%2C%20by%20nature%2C%20honest%20people%2C%20but%20you%20should%20be%20double-checking%20regardless.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20books%20that%20prosecutors%20presented%20were%20written%20when%20Trump%20was%20a%20businessman%2C%20not%20yet%20best%20known%20as%20a%20political%20figure.%20But%20prosecutors%20suggest%20his%20thoughtfulness%20about%20his%20bills%20continued%20into%20his%20presidency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECohen%20met%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrumps-former-cfo-will-plead-guilty-to-ny-fraud-trial-perjury-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAllen%20Weisselberg%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20now-former%20Trump%20Organization%20CFO%2C%20in%20January%20of%202017%20to%20hash%20out%20how%20he'd%20get%20reimbursed%20by%20Trump%20and%20the%20Trump%20Organization%2C%20according%20to%20records%20shown%20at%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20Weisselberg%20agreed%20to%20give%20Cohen%20%24420%2C000%20in%20multiple%20payments%20over%20the%20course%20of%202017%2C%20which%20would%20cover%20taxes%20and%20include%20a%20bonus%2C%20Weisselberg's%20deputy%20Jeffrey%20McConney%20testified.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225441%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Madeleine%20Westerhout%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5d5b07cdcd97845efd2973d3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223627%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMadeleine%20Westehout%20had%20a%20desk%20right%20outside%20the%20Oval%20Office%20and%20watched%20him%20sign%20documents%20while%20in%20meetings%2C%20she%20testified.%3Cp%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%2F%20Getty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Trump%20was%20running%20the%20Trump%20Organization%20every%20day%2C%20it%20was%20easy%20to%20get%20ahold%20of%20him%20in%20his%20Trump%20Tower%20office%20to%20approve%20expenses%20and%20sign%20checks%20paying%20for%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20with%20him%20in%20the%20White%20House%2C%20employees%20had%20to%20figure%20out%20another%20way%20to%20have%20him%20sign%20off%20on%20expenses.%20They%20devised%20a%20system%20where%20they'd%20cut%20the%20checks%20and%20print%20invoices%20in%20New%20York%2C%20then%20FedEx%20a%20pile%20of%20them%20to%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20a%20few%20times%20a%20month.%20They'd%20pass%20through%20the%20hands%20of%20Trump's%20bodyguard-turned-White%20House%20employee%20Keith%20Schiller%2C%20then%20make%20their%20way%20to%20the%20Oval%20Office.%20Trump%20would%20review%20and%20sign%20them%2C%20and%20then%20send%20them%20back%20to%20Manhattan%20%E2%80%94%20all%20with%20the%20logistical%20assistance%20of%20taxpayer-funded%20government%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Trump%20didn't%20automatically%20put%20his%20signature%20on%20every%20check.%20Occasionally%2C%20he'd%20write%20%26quot%3BVOID%26quot%3B%20on%20one%20he%20didn't%20want%20to%20be%20paid%2C%20according%20to%20Trump%20Organization%20employee%20Deborah%20Tarassoff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20signed%20in%20a%20Sharpie%20in%20black%2C%26quot%3B%20Tarassoff%20testified.%20%26quot%3BThat%20is%20what%20he%20usually%20uses.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Trump%20was%20making%20life-or-death%20decisions%20in%20the%20Oval%20Office%2C%20the%20billionaire%20was%20also%20discerning%20about%20trivial-seeming%20expenses.%20Prosecutors%20presented%20an%20invoice%20from%20the%20Winged%20Foot%20Golf%20Club%2C%20located%20north%20of%20New%20York%20City%2C%20for%20Trump's%20dues%2C%20that%20was%20sent%20to%20the%20White%20House%20from%20New%20York.%20Rhona%20Graff%2C%20his%20executive%20assistant%20at%20the%20Trump%20Organization%2C%20asked%20if%20he%20wanted%20to%20suspend%20his%20membership%20for%20four%20years%20%E2%80%94%20or%20to%20%26quot%3Bcontinue%20paying%20annual%20dues%20%2B%20the%20food%20minimum.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20wrote%20in%20felt-tip%20pen%3A%20%26quot%3BPay-%20ASAP%20OK%26quot%3B%20and%20signed%20%26quot%3BD.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221482%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Winged%20Foot%20golf%20club%20invoice%20trump%20manhattan%20trial%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663e31b0b4abc992e8c7f978%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221334%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDonald%20Trump%20approved%20paying%20dues%20to%20a%20Westchester%20golf%20club%20while%20juggling%20the%20job%20of%20the%20presidency%2C%20as%20shown%20in%20these%20notes%20presented%20at%20trial.%3Cp%3EManhattan%20district%20attorney's%20office%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20was%20included%20in%20the%20stack%20of%20checks%2C%20so%20I%20passed%20it%20along%2C%26quot%3B%20Westerhout%2C%20Trump's%20White%20House%20executive%20assistant%20in%202017%2C%20testified%20at%20the%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWesterhout%20didn't%20send%20back%20every%20single%20check%20to%20the%20Trump%20Organization.%20Sometimes%2C%20Trump%20didn't%20pull%20out%20his%20Sharpie%20(sometimes%20a%20Pentel%20felt-tip%20pen%2C%20she%20testified)%20to%20sign%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERebecca%20Manochio%2C%20the%20bookkeeper%20at%20the%20Trump%20Organization%20who%20was%20first%20to%20handle%20the%20checks%20when%20they%20came%20from%20the%20White%20House%2C%20testified%20that%20sometimes%20checks%20would%20be%20missing.%20When%20that%20happened%2C%20she%20checked%20with%20Westerhout.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEither%20it%20got%20lost%2C%20or%20he%20had%20questions%20about%20it%2C%20and%20he%20had%20to%20speak%20to%20someone%2C%26quot%3B%20Manochio%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Trump%20had%20a%20question%20about%20a%20check%2C%20he'd%20talk%20with%20a%20Trump%20Organization%20employee%20about%20it%2C%20Westerhout%20testified.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20I%20remember%2C%20maybe%2C%20a%20couple%20times%20him%20having%20a%20question%20about%20a%20check%20and%20then%20calling%20Allen%20Weisselberg%20or%20somebody%20else%20in%20the%20Trump%20Organization%20to%20ask%20for%20clarification%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGraff%2C%20for%20her%20part%2C%20testified%20that%20%26quot%3Bit%20wasn't%20unusual%26quot%3B%20to%20see%20Trump%20on%20the%20phone%20while%20signing%20checks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAm%20I%20correct%20that%20when%20he%20would%20sign%20checks%2C%20he%20was%20often%20multitasking%3F%26quot%3B%20Necheles%20asked%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20happened%20on%20occasion%2C%26quot%3B%20Graff%20answered.%20%26quot%3BIt%20would%20depend%20what%20was%20going%20on%20at%20the%20moment%20and%20how%20important%20the%20checks%20were%20that%20needed%20to%20be%20signed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20%E2%80%94%20now%20a%20commensurate%20multitasker%20as%20he%20defends%20himself%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-key-cases-civil-criminal-investigations-lawsuits-updates-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emultiple%20civil%20and%20criminal%20cases%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20employed%20a%20similar%20legal%20defense%20in%20his%20civil%20fraud%20case%20last%20year%2C%20where%20the%20New%20York%20Attorney%20General's%20Office%20accused%20him%20and%20his%20company%20of%20fudging%20numbers%20to%20commit%20insurance%2C%20bank%2C%20and%20tax%20fraud.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20deposition%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-busy-saving-world-from-nuclear-holocaust-commit-business-fraud-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%2