nd%20compete%20with%20China%20on%20the%20economic%20front%2C%20External%20Affairs%20Minister%20S%20Jaishankar%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20under%20the%20leadership%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20has%20been%20focusing%20on%20enhancing%20domestic%20manufacturing%20in%20the%20last%2010%20years%20as%20there%20was%20a%20neglect%20of%20the%20sector%20before%202014%20and%20it%20created%20many%20problems%20for%20the%20country%2C%20Jaishankar%20told%20PTI%20in%20an%20exclusive%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20suggested%20that%20lack%20of%20focus%20in%20the%20past%20to%20the%20manufacturing%20sector%20is%20linked%20to%20the%20upward%20trajectory%20in%20India-China%20trade%20notwithstanding%20New%20Delhi's%20position%20that%20normalisation%20of%20ties%20with%20Beijing%20is%20dependent%20on%20the%20resolution%20of%20the%20eastern%20Ladakh%20border%20row.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20need%20to%20be%20confident.%20I%20am%20clear%20that%20international%20politics%2C%20international%20relations%20are%20competitive.%20I%20have%20a%20neighbour%20like%20China.%20I%20have%20to%20learn%20to%20compete%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBy%20my%20complaining%2C%20China%20is%20not%20going%20to%20stop%20doing%20things.%20If%20I%20do%20not%20build%20up%20my%20strength%20at%20home%2C%20our%20foreign%20policy%20will%20be%20as%20good%20as%20our%20domestic%20policy%2C%26quot%3B%20Jaishankar%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20a%20function%20of%20our%20domestic%20policy%20that%20if%20I%20can%20actually%20build%20up%20my%20economy%2C%20if%20I%20can%20build%20up%20my%20manufacturing%2C%20if%20I%20can%20create%20the%20kind%20of%20capabilities%20which%20today%20I%20am%20trying%20to%20do%2C%20I%20think%20you%20are%20going%20to%20find%20foreign%20policy%20has%20much%20more%20resources%20and%20much%20more%20tool%20in%20its%20toolkit%20to%20actually%20influence%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20response%20came%20when%20asked%20why%20India's%20bilateral%20trade%20volume%20with%20China%20is%20going%20up%20when%20New%20Delhi%20has%20been%20insisting%20that%20ties%20cannot%20be%20normal%20if%20the%20border%20situation%20is%20abnormal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJaishankar%20suggested%20that%20such%20a%20scenario%20has%20arisen%20as%20adequate%20attention%20to%20the%20manufacturing%20sector%20was%20not%20given%20before%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20and%20Chinese%20militaries%20have%20been%20locked%20in%20a%20standoff%20since%20May%202020%20and%20a%20full%20resolution%20of%20the%20border%20row%20has%20not%20yet%20been%20achieved%20though%20the%20two%20sides%20have%20disengaged%20from%20a%20number%20of%20friction%20points.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20it%20is%20common%20sense%20that%20if%20there%20is%20no%20peace%20and%20tranquillity%20in%20the%20border%2C%20how%20can%20you%20have%20a%20normal%20relationship%2C%26quot%3B%20Jaishankar%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAfter%20all%20if%20somebody%20is%20at%20your%20front%20door%20in%20an%20unfriendly%20manner%2C%20you%20are%20not%20going%20to%20go%20out%20there%20and%20act%20as%20though%20everything%20is%20normal.%20That%20to%20me%20is%20a%20straightforward%20proposition%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20been%20consistently%20maintaining%20that%20peace%20and%20tranquillity%20along%20the%20LAC%20were%20key%20for%20normalisation%20of%20overall%20ties.%20However%2C%20trade%20between%20the%20two%20countries%20is%20steadily%20expanding.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20last%20decade%2C%20bilateral%20trade%20between%20India%20and%20China%20recorded%20significant%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%202015%20to%202022%2C%20India-China%20bilateral%20trade%20grew%20by%2090.14%20per%20cent%2C%20an%20average%20yearly%20growth%20of%2012.87%20per%20cent.%20In%202022%2C%20the%20overall%20trade%20with%20China%20increased%20by%208.47%20per%20cent%20year%20on%20year%20to%20reach%20USD%20136.26%20billion%2C%20crossing%20the%20USD%20100%20billion%20mark%20for%20a%20second%20time%20in%20a%20row%2C%20according%20to%20official%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20trade%20deficit%20came%20at%20USD%20101.28%20billion%20as%20India's%20imports%20from%20China%20witnessed%20major%20increase.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20the%20government%20has%20been%20making%20efforts%20to%20expand%20manufacturing%20in%20a%20number%20of%20critical%20areas%20as%20part%20of%20an%20aim%20to%20de-risking%20from%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20talk%20about%20trade%2C%20what%20has%20happened%20is%20in%20many%20ways%2C%20the%20fact%20that%20we%20actually%20neglected%20manufacturing%20in%20this%20country.%20That%20in%20many%20ways%2C%20we%20did%20not%20give%20the%20kind%20of%20support%20to%20our%20manufacturers%2C%20especially%20our%20small%20and%20medium%20enterprises%2C%26quot%3B%20Jaishankar%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20external%20affairs%20minister%20listed%20various%20initiatives%20rolled%20out%20by%20the%20Modi%20government%2C%20including%20the%20'Make%20in%20India'%20and%20'Production%20Linked%20Incentive'%20(PLI)%20schemes%2C%20to%20enhance%20domestic%20manufacturing%20%26quot%3BIn%20fact%20when%20Make%20in%20India%20was%20started%2C%20you%20have%20people%20who%20even%20laughed%20at%20it.%20Even%20now%20there%20are%20people%20like%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20who%20believe%20that%20we%20are%20incapable%20of%20manufacturing%20in%20this%20country%20and%20there%20are%20some%20economists%20who%20also%20have%20that%20kind%20of%20view%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%2C%20the%20fact%20that%20our%20manufacturing%20fell%20behind%2C%20I%20think%2C%20has%20created%20many%20of%20the%20problems%20that%20today%20we%20are%20experiencing%20today.%20You%20cannot%20get%20an%20immediate%20fix%20but%20what%20you%20can%20do%2C%20which%20we%20have%20been%20trying%20to%20do%2C%20is%20actually%20to%20boo